1. What is Java?
------------------------------------------------------------

Java is a high-level, object-oriented, class-based, platform-independent programming language.

It was developed by James Gosling at Sun Microsystems in 1991 and officially released in 1995.

Now Java is owned by Oracle Corporation.

Java follows the principle:

Write Once, Run Anywhere (WORA)

------------------------------------------------------------
2. History of Java
------------------------------------------------------------

• Developed by James Gosling.
• Original name: Oak.
• Later renamed to Java.
• Released in 1995 by Sun Microsystems.
• Oracle acquired Sun Microsystems in 2010.

